# Splunk SPL Queries

All queries designed for Windows event log data. Adjust index, sourcetype, and field names based on your Splunk configuration.

## T1566.001 - Spearphishing Attachment

Identifies office applications spawning command interpreters.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
parent_process_name IN (winword.exe, excel.exe, powerpnt.exe)
process_name IN (powershell.exe, cmd.exe, wscript.exe, cscript.exe)
| stats count as event_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by parent_process_name, process_name, host, process_path
| where event_count >= 1
| sort - event_count
```

## T1059.001 - Obfuscated PowerShell Execution

Detects PowerShell processes with encoding and obfuscation indicators.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1 process_name=powershell.exe
(process_command_line="*-EncodedCommand*" OR
 process_command_line="*IEX (New-Object Net.WebClient*" OR
 process_command_line="*Invoke-Expression*" OR
 process_command_line="*[Convert]::FromBase64String*" OR
 process_command_line="*DownloadString*")
| stats count as event_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen,
    values(user) as users, values(host) as devices
    by process_command_line, host, os
| where event_count >= 1
| sort - event_count
```

## T1003 - OS Credential Dumping

Identifies credential dumping tool execution and commands.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
(parent_process_name IN (mimikatz.exe, procdump.exe, ntdsutil.exe) OR
 process_command_line="*sekurlsa::logonpasswords*" OR
 process_command_line="*sekurlsa::ekeys*" OR
 process_command_line="*-ma lsass*" OR
 process_command_line="*lsadump::sam*" OR
 process_command_line="*lsadump::secrets*")
NOT (process_command_line="*Picus*" OR process_command_line="*Qualys*" OR
     process_command_line="*Rapid7*" OR process_command_line="*Tenable*")
| stats count as event_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by parent_process_name, process_command_line, host, user
| where event_count >= 1
| sort - event_count
```

## T1574.002 - DLL Side-loading

Detects suspicious DLL execution from non-standard paths.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Sysmon EventCode=3
file_name="*.dll"
(file_path="*\\Users\\Public\\*" OR
 file_path="*\\Temp\\*" OR
 file_path="*\\ProgramData\\*" OR
 file_path="*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp*")
NOT (file_path="*Windows Update*" OR file_path="*SoftwareDistribution*" OR
     file_path="*Microsoft Defender*" OR file_path="*Windows Defender*")
| stats count as event_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by file_name, file_path, host
| where event_count >= 1
| sort - event_count
```

## T1071.001 - Suspicious C2 Connections

Identifies HTTPS connections to suspicious TLDs.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=5156 Direction=Outbound
DestinationPort=443 Protocol=tcp
(DestinationDomain="*.ru" OR DestinationDomain="*.ir" OR
 DestinationDomain="*.gq" OR DestinationDomain="*.tk" OR
 DestinationDomain="*.ml" OR DestinationDomain="*.ga")
NOT (DestinationDomain="*.yandex.ru" OR DestinationDomain="*.vk.com" OR
     DestinationDomain="*.rambler.ru" OR DestinationDomain="*.mail.ru" OR
     DestinationDomain IN ("microsoft.com", "google.com", "cloudflare.com"))
| stats count as connection_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen,
    values(process_name) as processes
    by DestinationDomain, DestinationPort, host
| where connection_count >= 1
| sort - connection_count
```

## T1547.001 - Registry-Based Persistence

Monitors Windows Run registry key modifications.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Sysmon EventCode=13
RegistryKey="*Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*"
NOT (RegistryKey="*Microsoft Edge Update*" OR
     RegistryKey="*MicrosoftEdgeAutoLaunch*" OR
     RegistryKey="*RtkAudUService*" OR
     RegistryKey="*OneDrive*" OR
     RegistryKey="*Windows Update*" OR
     RegistryKey="*WindowsUpdate*")
| stats count as modification_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by RegistryKey, RegistryKeyPath, RegistryValue, host, process_name, user
| where modification_count >= 1
| sort - modification_count
```

## T1218 - LOLBin Abuse

Detects LOLBins with suspicious command-line parameters.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
process_name IN (regsvcs.exe, regasm.exe, mshta.exe, rundll32.exe, certutil.exe, certreq.exe)
(process_command_line="*http://*" OR process_command_line="*https://*" OR
 process_command_line="*hxxp://*" OR process_command_line="*hxxps://*" OR
 process_command_line="*.dll*" OR process_command_line="*javascript:*" OR
 process_command_line="*vbscript:*")
NOT (process_command_line="*spool*" OR process_command_line="*Prnntfy.dll*" OR
     process_command_line="*pla.dll*" OR process_command_line="*printui.dll*" OR
     process_command_line="*Windows\\System32*" OR process_command_line="*Program Files*")
| stats count as command_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by process_name, process_command_line, host, user
| where command_count >= 1
| sort - command_count
```

## T1027 - Obfuscation & Encoding

Identifies script execution with obfuscation indicators.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
process_name IN (powershell.exe, cscript.exe, wscript.exe, mshta.exe, regsvr32.exe, rundll32.exe)
(process_command_line="*-EncodedCommand*" OR
 process_command_line="*frombase64string*" OR
 process_command_line="*powershell -e*" OR
 process_command_line="*powershell /e*" OR
 process_command_line="*powershell -enc*" OR
 process_command_line="*powershell /enc*" OR
 process_command_line="*mshta vbscript:*" OR
 process_command_line="*javascript:*" OR
 process_command_line="*[convert]::frombase64*" OR
 process_command_line="*System.Convert*")
NOT (process_command_line="*Nutanix*" OR process_command_line="*VMware*" OR
     process_command_line="*Hyper-V*" OR user="SYSTEM" OR user="NETWORK SERVICE")
| stats count as event_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by process_name, process_command_line, host, user
| where event_count >= 1
| sort - event_count
```

## T1567.002 - Data Exfiltration Over Web

Detects file transfer utilities with web protocols.

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
process_name IN (curl.exe, wget.exe, ftp.exe)
(process_command_line="*http://*" OR
 process_command_line="*https://*" OR
 process_command_line="*ftp://*" OR
 process_command_line="*ftps://*")
NOT (user="SYSTEM" AND process_path="C:\\Windows\\System32\\*") AND
NOT (process_command_line="*Windows Update*" OR process_command_line="*Microsoft Update*" OR
     process_command_line="*NuGet*")
| stats count as command_count, min(_time) as first_seen, max(_time) as last_seen
    by process_name, process_command_line, host, user
| where command_count >= 1
| sort - command_count
```

