## Query Optimization Tips

### Time Window Filtering

Add time constraints to improve performance:

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security earliest=-30d@d latest=now() EventCode=1
parent_process_name IN (winword.exe, excel.exe, powerpnt.exe)
process_name IN (powershell.exe, cmd.exe, wscript.exe)
```

### Reduce Query Scope

Filter by hostname or asset group:

```spl
index=main host IN (server1, server2, server3, server4)
sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
```

### Data Model Acceleration

Use Splunk Data Models for faster execution:

```spl
| from datamodel: Endpoint.Processes
| search parent_process="winword.exe" process="powershell.exe"
| stats count by host, user
```

---

## Alert Configuration

### Create Detection Alert

1. Save search as alert
2. Configure trigger: `When result count > 0`
3. Set severity: High
4. Notification: Email/Slack to SOC team
5. Add context fields: host, user, process_command_line

### Example Alert Creation

```spl
index=main sourcetype=WinEventLog:Security EventCode=1
parent_process_name IN (winword.exe, excel.exe, powerpnt.exe)
process_name IN (powershell.exe, cmd.exe, wscript.exe)
| stats count as EventCount, values(process_command_line) as Commands,
    values(user) as Users, values(host) as Hosts
    by parent_process_name, process_name
| where EventCount > 0
```

Set Alert Action:
- Alert Name: "Spearphishing Attachment - Office Spawning Shell"
- Severity: High
- Trigger on: EventCount > 0
- Throttle: 1 incident per 30 minutes per host

